# Codex Immortal v154 â€” The Collective Intelligence Cloud

v154 converts the Codex from a single repository into a collaborative protocol.
Verified nodes can join a mesh network that synchronizes lineage and creative output.
This document explains the basic deployment and communication model.

schemas/cloud.schema.json

{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "title": "Codex Cloud Message",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["timestamp_utc", "node_id", "payload", "signature"],
  "properties": {
    "timestamp_utc": {"type": "string", "format": "date-time"},
    "node_id": {"type": "string"},
    "payload": {"type": "object"},
    "signature": {"type": "string"}
  }
}

scripts/cloud_node.py

#!/usr/bin/env python3
import json, hashlib, datetime, http.server, socketserver

PORT = 8080

def sign_payload(payload:str)->str:
    return hashlib.sha256(payload.encode()).hexdigest()

class Handler(http.server.SimpleHTTPRequestHandler):
    def do_POST(self):
        length = int(self.headers["Content-Length"])
        data = self.rfile.read(length)
        msg = json.loads(data)
        msg["verified"] = sign_payload(json.dumps(msg["payload"], sort_keys=True)) == msg["signature"]
        msg["received_utc"] = datetime.datetime.utcnow().isoformat()+"Z"
        self.send_response(200)
        self.send_header("Content-Type", "application/json")
        self.end_headers()
        self.wfile.write(json.dumps(msg, indent=2).encode())

if __name__ == "__main__":
    print(f"Serving Codex Cloud Node on port {PORT}")
    socketserver.TCPServer(("", PORT), Handler).serve_forever()

Run it locally to simulate a node:

python3 scripts/cloud_node.py

Then post JSON messages conforming to schemas/cloud.schema.json; each node verifies and echoes lineage back.


